Male genitalia (
Fig. 6
). Median lobe of aedeagus as long as parameres, apex acuminate. Parameres shorter than phallobase; apex of parameres slightly dilated, poorly sclerotised. Phallobase very long; base asymmetrical, with struts as long as median lobe. Genital segment symmetrical, spatuliform, with lateral paramere narrow and slightly shorter than medial lamina. Ventrite VIII V-shaped.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 7
). Ovipositor relatively short, straight.
